<br>
For the past two weeks Tish (my level 26 necro RL wife) and I have been in Permafrost. I wanted to get runed circlets, arch bags, and wolf fur slippers for both of us. At our level the preacher and archaeologist are pretty easy so we got those two items in short order. So then we started moving into the other half of Perma, turning right at the flag room instead of left.<br>
<br>
We almost always fight our way from the gate to the scryer room, because I distrust invis, and dislike having nowhere to retreat because we didn't clean out the goblins behind us. Not to mention that some spawn spots seem to make goblins that almost always see through invis. So we fight from the gate, past the alchemist area, and down to the tight area just outside the scryer's room. This is very time consuming and sometimes pulls go bad. We are forced to gate and start over, things like that.<br>
<br>
Once we are outside the scryer, the hard part begins. The scryer room at full spawn has 7 goblins in it, plus one outside the door. And if there's a scryer actually in there, its even rougher because he can be a white con to me. Breaking this room at our level is TOUGH. My wife uses her mez, she uses FD, she uses engulfing darkness, yet the slightest thing goes wrong and we're both dead. We had a monk join us once and the room became a cinch, but its very rare that players of our level come to Permafrost hoping to join a group.<br>
<br>
So, we med outside the room, usually leaving a couple goblins inside alive so as to break up the timing of the spawn a bit. Besides, it would be stupid to med inside the room, or to even fight inside it. We'd get mobbed. <br>
<br>
If you have an impression of the effort we've put forth to get this scryer, you understand the reason for this rant. On no less than four occasions some high level jerk has run straight past us, killed every goblin in the room, then walked right out past us again. We've had two scryers stolen from us this way. One was visibly holding a staff, the other was holding nothing, which indicates he had the slippers.<br>
<br>
And that's not the end of it. High level jerks tromp around all over like they own the place. I've had preachers, archaeologists, scryers, and alchemists stolen from me. Sometimes they wander around and kill every blue con goblin in a two mile radius, meaning I won't get any experience for the next half hour. Heck, sometimes entire guilds come in and commit goblin genocide, then laugh at me when I complain. Other times they just go in, kill the one rare spawn they want, then without warning train half the dungeon to the zone. Uh, thanks Mr. High Level Jerk, I'll deal with that train when it comes back for me. Or maybe I'll just gate out and find you've taken my camp when you get back.<br>
<br>
Now don't get me wrong. I know not all high level farmers are jerks. Many's the time when some nice druid or shaman in the alchemist's cave will regen my pet or give me words that dropped. Sometimes they offer help when I run into trouble. I understand completely that Permafrost is almost a low level Lower Guk style treasure trove, and that it's hard to hunt there when you are of a level to actually get experience. Permafrost is a great place to go and peacefully solo at high levels, and maybe get some decent loot to earn some cash. But please don't trample the little guys who have the guts to go in there and try to actually gain experience and really *earn* those nice loot items.<br>
<br>
I shall close with a transcript of an actual encounter I had with a high level jerk. Names have been changed to protect the idiots:<br>
<br>
Rainman the barbarian Myrmidon goes into Permafrost, kills every goblin in the jail and scryer area, and steals the scryer.<br>
<br>
Me: &quot;I can't believe you just killed every goblin within pulling distance AND stole the scryer I was camping. I guess I won't be getting any experience for the next half hour.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rainmain: &quot;Sorry I was just passing through, saw the scryer was up so I killed it. I didn't know you were camping it. If you're camping a spawn you shouldn't sit halfway across the dungeon.&quot;<br>
<br>
Me: &quot;I was sitting just outside the room!&quot;<br>
<br>
Rainman: &quot;Well next time sit inside the room.&quot;<br>
<br>
Me: &quot;There were four goblins in there, and I was OOM! Sitting inside that room would be suicide!&quot;<br>
<br>
Rainman: &quot;Well, the scryer didn't drop anything anyway.&quot;<br>
<br>
Me: &quot;Uh huh, sure he didn't.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rainman: &quot;Seriously, he just had some cloth shoes which I destroyed.&quot;<br>
<br>
Me: &quot;!&quot;<br>
<br>
Rainman: &quot;Hey, can I have a coldstone?&quot;<br>
<br>
I was so disgusted I decided to run to Halas and bank the 8 pieces of bronze armor I was carrying. Bronze armor still sells quite well to players on my server. I was carrying it in dim pockets because I couldn't move otherwise. On the way to Halas my client crashed and I lost it all. True story. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 28th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> fg2010</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(10/3/00 5:32:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   You have to SHARE</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
I play a mage as well.<br>
<br>
Just a word of advice in 10 or 15 levels you will be one of those high level guys &quot;thinking you own the place&quot;.<br>
<br>
I'm only in the 30s levels and I have people at level 20 or so at high keep yelling at me for trying to get the PGT for my palidian friends.<br>
<br>
No one owns a spawn site.  Your fighting a loosing battle if you think you do because VI will NOT back you up, at the very best they will tell everyone to either leave or share.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
