 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#333333>(10/3/00 6:30:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: You have to SHARE</span><hr size=1> I have played another character to just past 50, and I have never, and will never knowingly steal a rare spawn from somebody else who's already camping it, regardless of their level. The mere suggestion that I would do such a thing is insulting, and I'm offended that you consider such a lack of honor to be acceptable behavior in a socially interactive environment like Everquest.<br>
<br>
You have to SHARE. Ha, very funny. Are you one of those people who pulls out the PNP rules when you're camping the lord in Lower Guk and decide you want to steal the magi spawn away from the people camping it? Or perhaps you bring your guild into Fear or Hate when another guild is already there and say &quot;You have to SHARE! Ha ha!&quot; Maybe one time you can recall racing past a large group that was occupied with King Tranix and whalloped Lord Nagafen before they could reach him?<br>
<br>
I'm willing to bet you didn't do any of those things, because they never happen. It's rudeness taken to the nth degree and nobody would stand for it. The only reason players can get away with such behavior in Permafrost is because its isolated and the big guy can trample all over the little guy. But just because you can get away with it doesn't make it right. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 31st Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> fg2010</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(10/3/00 9:35:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Self-Centered people.</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
Your insulted?  I'm tired of running into self-centered people.. its not just on EQ eiter any MMOG.<br>
I am sick of wasting my hard earned money just to fight with people like you to be even allowed the opprotunity to try to get my fair share.<br>
<br>
It sounds to me like your extreamly self-centered.  On the one hand you claim these high level people are stealing your spawn.. on the other hand your basically pointing out that its your spawn because you were there for 8+ or whatever hours camping it.  Hey thats your choice, I would rather be getting steady exp and ok loot somewhere else so I could level.<br>
<br>
So you have played a character to 50, well I haven't.. only been to level 46 as a palidian.. and then promptly lost numerous levels due to various mistakes (all I can take full responsibility for).. I ended up deleting the pally in disgust and taking a few months off.<br>
<br>
I happen to like playing a mage much more.. lots more fun.<br>
<br>
According to VI (not me or any other player) YOU DON'T OWN THE SPAWN AND YOU HAVE TO SHARE.  The only time VI makes exceptions to these rules are with the plains and with VP.  in those areas the most powerful guilds as you know are in control and monopolizing the areas with VIs unofficial approval.  If your not in one of these guilds you don't go to the plains.  This is the way it will always be because the Plains are a tough place that requires organization.  Spawns are not shared there.  Everywhere else.. well according to VI spawns have to be shared.. its as simple as that.<br>
<br>
They made the policy I did not.. and if they change it I will abide by it.  Sure I wait my turn, when its worth it.  If its not I leave and go somewhere else.  If people hassle me I petition, in every time someone has shown up due to a petition I have been vindicated.<br>
<br>
I was once forced to give up a damn PGT I could have hocked for some plat (not much.. but enough to help with spells) to a bunch of people 10 or so levels lower after they said I could share the site.. who forced me?  My guild.. not the GMs .. the guides/GMs said &quot;you made the kill.. its yours&quot;.<br>
<br>
